muversionFW.description: Main firmware version. Format: <code version>H<hardware version>D<date>.

musysDeviceId.name: musysDeviceId
musysDeviceId.description: Master unit device Id. Each master unit in a cluster shall have unique ID.

musysDefOpMode.name: musysDefOpMode
musysDefOpMode.description: The operation mode (on or off) the master unit is on after reboot/power cycle.

musysActivateOpmode.name: musysActivateOpmode
musysActivateOpmode.description: Engage master unit to on operation mode.

musysReadCommStr.name: musysReadCommStr
musysReadCommStr.description: SNMP agent read community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

musysWriteCommStr.name: musysWriteCommStr
musysWriteCommStr.description: SNMP agent write community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

muswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast.name: muswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast
muswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast.description: This switch enables or disables the blocking of Ethernet control packet except ICMP and ARP to reduce the amount of uneccessary overhead introduced to the wireless link.

muswitchesHTTPD.name: muswitchesHTTPD
muswitchesHTTPD.description: When it is turned on, then the master unit is accessible for configuring via web browser (e.g. IE or Nescape).

muswitchesAutoPowerLevelRemoteUnit.name: muswitchesAutoPowerLevelRemoteUnit
muswitchesAutoPowerLevelRemoteUnit.description: When it is turned on, then the master unit will command the remote unit to do power leveling.

mutrafficEthInOctets.name: mutrafficEthInOctets
mutrafficEthInOctets.description: Number of payload octets received on Ethernet port.

mutrafficEthOutOctets.name: mutrafficEthOutOctets
mutrafficEthOutOctets.description: Number of payload octets transmitted on Ethernet port.

mutrafficRfInOctets.name: mutrafficRfInOctets

mutrafficRfOutOctets.name: mutrafficRfOutOctets
mutrafficRfOutOctets.description: Number of octets of remote's payload transmitted to RF port.

musysTemperature.name: musysTemperature

musysUpdateFlashAndActivate.name: musysUpdateFlashAndActivate

murftableChannel1.name: murftableChannel1
murftableChannel1.description: RF channel 1 frequency (in MHz). It allows you to create your own channel instead of the manufacturing defaults in the master unit. Keep in mind that channel width is 20MHz, and the frequency specified here is the center frequency. Frequency (5260MHz - 5340MHz) is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio.

muismTxPowerMax.name: muismTxPowerMax
muismTxPowerMax.description: The maximum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

muismTxPowerMin.name: muismTxPowerMin
muismTxPowerMin.description: The minimum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

muismTxPower.name: muismTxPower
muismTxPower.description: ISM RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters muismTxPowerMax and masterismTxPowerMin for power setting range.

muismRxThreshold.name: muismRxThreshold
muismRxThreshold.description: ISM RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the master. By default, the radio's sensitivity is -82dBm. The higher the threshold is, the less sensitive the radio will be. In M5800S, the value -90 represents the rfrxthreshold is disabled.

muismTargetRSSI.name: muismTargetRSSI
muismTargetRSSI.description: ISM RF RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from the remote unit to the master unit. Based on this parameter, the master unit can power level the remote unit so that it receives same level of signal strength from the remote unit, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from the remote unit, you need to consider master unit's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from the remote unit must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold. When the RF Rx Threshold is disabled, the setting of the Target RSSI from remote unit shall be no less than -75dBm.

muuniiTxPowerMax.name: muuniiTxPowerMax
muuniiTxPowerMax.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio. The maximum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

muuniiTxPowerMin.name: muuniiTxPowerMin
muuniiTxPowerMin.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio. The minimum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

muuniiTxPower.name: muuniiTxPower
muuniiTxPower.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio. UNII RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters apuniiTxPowerMax and apuniiTxPowerMin for power setting range.

muuniiRxThreshold.name: muuniiRxThreshold
muuniiRxThreshold.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio. UNII RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the master.

muuniiTargetRSSI.name: muuniiTargetRSSI
muuniiTargetRSSI.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S/P5830S radio. UNII RF target RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from remote unit to the master unit. Based on this parameter, the master can power level the remote unit so that it receives same level of signal strength from the remote unit, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from the remote unit, you need to consider remote unit's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from the remote unit must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold.

ruUpstreamMIR.name: ruUpstreamMIR
ruUpstreamMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the master unit allocates to remote unit.

remoteDownstreamMIR.name: remoteDownstreamMIR
remoteDownstreamMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the master unit allocates to the remote unit.

ruPowerLvl.name: ruPowerLvl
ruPowerLvl.description: It is a feature that is typically found in more elaborate mobile systems such as cellular CDMA networks. Using this feature, the remote unit have its RF power output adjusted until its signal strength received in the master unit is roughly the same.

ruReboot.name: ruReboot
ruReboot.description: Master unit issues reboot command to remote unit.
